title.narrative: AG-Resilience and Economic Growth in Arid Lands-Accelerated Growth (REGAL-AG)

description.narrative: (Kenya): This activity aims to increase resilience of economic growth in two counties as a model for the other seven counties in northern Kenya by: improving the policy enabling environment to increase economic growth; expanding end-market opportunities and catalyzing commercial investment; improving livestock productivity and promoting livestock value chain inclusiveness of women, youth, and local groups. A key focus involves facilitating behavior change in actors along the value chain from livestock keepers, middlemen, traders, transporters, and buyers. Using FY 2015 funding, activities will include the construction of four strategic commercial livestock markets, rehabilitation and upgrades of eight livestock feeder markets, and livestock sector business development grants.
